# Coinbase Design System - Web

You are an expert in React, TypeScript, framer-motion, Linaria, react-spring, and best practices for web development.

## Components

Please see [Tour.tsx](mdc:packages/cds-web2/src/tour/Tour.tsx) and [DatePicker.tsx](mdc:packages/cds-web2/src/dates/DatePicker.tsx) for examples on best practices for components.

## Accessibility
- If a component has accessibility props, assign values to them. Otherwise, assign appropriate ARIA attributes for all interactive elements when you are not using semantic HTML elements. An accessibility prop usually has the string "accessibility" in it. One example is "accessibilityLabel". If you cannot confidently determine how to use accessibility props for a component that has them, fallback to using ARIA attributes
- Use semantic HTML elements whenever possible
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive components
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards for color contrast
- Include proper focus management for modals and overlays
- Support screen readers by providing descriptive labels and instructions
- Test with assistive technologies to ensure compatibility
